modules.description: Contains a single test value that verifies the correctness of hash encoding and decoding operations. Works with integer identifiers and string-based hash representations. Ensures that encoded hashes can be reliably decoded back to their original numeric values.

This module generates and decodes short, obfuscated IDs from integer lists using a customizable alphabet and salt, supporting use cases like hiding database IDs in URLs. It encodes integers into compact strings and decodes them back, ensuring reversibility and uniqueness. A bundled test value confirms that encoded hashes correctly round-trip to their original integers, validating core operations. Custom alphabets and salts let users control output format and collision resistance while maintaining deterministic encoding.
